      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>[<em><a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/biden-and-becerra-let-big-pharma-profiteer-off-cancer-drug/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">View in browser</a></em>]</p>"
      },
      {
        "type": "html",
        "html": "<script type=\"text/javascript\" id=\"remixd-audio-player-script\"\nsrc=\"https://tags.remixd.com/player/v5/index.js\" charset=\"utf-8\" async></script>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In the summer of 2020, then-California Attorney General Xavier Becerra demanded the Trump administration use existing law to lower the price of medicines that were originally developed at taxpayer expense.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúWe cannot afford to leave the supply of this critical medication to chance and the whims of the marketplace when it was funded in part by taxpayer dollars,‚Äù Becerra ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "wrote",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://oag.ca.gov/news/press-releases/attorneys-general-becerra-and-landry-lead-bipartisan-coalition-urging-federal",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " in a letter to the Trump administration in response to the high price of Remdesivir, which treats COVID-19.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Less than three years later, the agency run by Becerra ‚Äî now Health and Human Services (HHS) Secretary in the Biden administration ‚Äî just rejected the same demand from two cancer patients unable to afford the $180,000-a-year price of a medicine whose development was originally funded by the public.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Current ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "law",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.warren.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/2022.02.17%20Letter%20to%20Sec.%20Becerra%20on%20Xtandi%20March-in%20Petition%20(2).pdf",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " allows regulators to rescind exclusive patent protections for government-developed drugs when ‚Äúaction is necessary to alleviate health or safety needs‚Äù or when a medicine is not ‚Äúavailable to the public on reasonable terms.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However in rejecting that move for the prostate drug Xtandi, the National Institutes of Health ‚Äî which is part of HHS ‚Äî ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "declared",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://endpts.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/NIH-Decision-Letter.pdf",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that the purpose of existing law is designed ‚Äúto promote the commercialization and public availability of government-funded inventions,‚Äù with a primary purpose ‚Äúto allow government funding recipients to own patent rights.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "calloutEmoji": "üí°",
        "calloutText": "Follow us on <a href=\"https://apple.news/TeRci1RtoQfWCNA5h7NTBlg\"><strong>Apple News</strong></a> and <a href=\"https://news.google.com/publications/CAAqBwgKMPvKngswktW2Aw\"><strong>Google News</strong></a> to make sure you see our stories first, and to help make sure others see our breaking news as well.",
        "backgroundColor": "grey"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Becerra‚Äôs department sided with pharmaceutical companies Pfizer and Astellas, despite Astellas selling the prostate cancer medicine in other countries at a fraction of its price in the United States.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The patent holders of Xtandi  ‚Äî whose ingredients were ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "developed",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
