            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.nytimes.com/1995/04/12/us/us-gives-up-right-to-control-drug-prices.html",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúUnderstandably, members of the public are concerned that the prices they pay are higher than those in other high-income countries,‚Äù the Biden administration wrote in a letter to cancer patients on Tuesday, adding that officials share ‚Äúyour concern about the high price of drugs and the burden it places on patients and their families, particularly the uninsured and the underinsured.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, the administration insisted that it was rejecting the petition to use so-called ‚Äúmarch-in rights‚Äù to seize the patents on Xtandi because the prostate cancer drug is ‚Äúwidely available to the public on the market.‚Äù",
            "type": "text",
