            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that most, if not all, major new drugs are originally developed with funding from the U.S. government. But at the urging of pharmaceutical lobbyists ‚Äî and as nearly a ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "quarter billion dollars",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.opensecrets.org/industries/totals.php?cycle=2022&ind=h4300",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " of pharmaceutical industry campaign cash flowed to both parties ‚Äî federal officials have refused to use their existing power to reduce the U.S. prices of those drugs.",
